article.headline: Yale 80, N.J. Tech 51
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- Alex Zampier scored 18 points to lead Yale to an 80-51 win over the New Jersey Institute of Technology on Wednesday night, sending the Highlanders to their 48th consecutive loss. Porter Braswell added 14 points for the Bulldogs (4-9), while Travis Pinick had 13 and Ross Morin finished with 10. Gary Garris had 19 points and 10 rebounds for NJIT (0-15), while Isaiah Wilkerson added 15 points. The teams traded the lead for most of the first half before Yale went ahead for good on Morin's jumper with 4:36 remaining, and the Bulldogs closed the half out with a 17-4 run to grab a 33-20 lead at the break. Yale then dominated NJIT in the second half, leading by as many as 31 points and maintaining double-digit leads throughout. NJIT has not won since it defeated Longwood on February 19, 2007.
